OL,3,CNational Rail 'warned' about repairs
OL,4,Cbefore pensioner struck by train
OL,6,FPeople in Wiltshire say they warned
OL,7,FNational Rail about the danger of
OL,8,Fclosing a footbridge over a railway
OL,9,Fline in the months prior to a
OL,10,Fpensioner being fatally struck by a
OL,11,Ftrain.
OL,13,FShirley Pope was walking her dog
OL,14,Facross a passive crossing - where
OL,15,Fpedestrians must perform their own
OL,16,Frisk assessment before heading across
OL,17,Fthe tracks - in Pewsey.
OL,19,FShe was hit by a locomotive travelling
OL,20,Fat almost 100mph shortly before 2pm on
OL,21,F26 February 2025, which killed her.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
