OL,3,CNational Rail 'warned' about repairs
OL,4,Cbefore pensioner struck by train
OL,6,FLiz added: "Ever since they've shut
OL,7,Fthe bridge, we've been trying to get
OL,8,Fthrough to the powers that be to ask
OL,9,Fexactly what's going on and when they
OL,10,Fwere going to reopen it.
OL,12,F"We were pushed and fiddled side to
OL,13,Fside and we did say 'something is
OL,14,Fgoing to happen, there is going to be
OL,15,Fan accident', because so many people
OL,16,Fare using the crossing."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
